<TEXT>
after the sunday night performance of oh 
calcutta cast members put on their clothes and went home 
billed as the worlds longest running erotic stage musical 
oh calcutta may tour nationally and in latin america but its 
broadway run is over executive producer maria di dia says it 
played 5959 performances 
the revue opened june 17 1969 at offbroadways eden theater 
newly named to emphasize the nudity in the show there were ten in 
the cast then the final performance had eight in the opening 
number taking off the robe and 11 in the finale as a few cast 
alumni returned for a final scamper in white robes and birthday 
suits 
oh calcutta moved to broadways belasco theater in 1971 
and closed in 1972 the production just ended opened sept 24 
1976 at the edison theater 
in 1969 nudity was burgeoning in offbroadway shows a trend 
that has since receded to an audience member who had not seen 
oh calcutta since its original opening there seemed to be 
less nudity but more vulgar words than remembered 
the show got its start when english critic kenneth tynan asked 
friends and acquaintances to write skits for a revue about the 
pursuit of happiness through sex contributors included himself 
jules feiffer dan greenburg john lennon leonard melfi sam 
shepard and sherman yellen 
the results showed startlingly little cleverness the program 
didnt reveal who wrote what saving author embarrassment 
</TEXT>
