red warning flags went out for threatened dry lightning 
storms in idaho and winds whipped flames around a brush fire in 
utah as dozens of fires burned in seven western states 
more than 900 lightning strikes were reported sunday in eastern 
oregon where firefighters had earlier managed to contain the worst 
of a halfdozen major forest fires crews were sent to investigate 
one new fire on the ochoco national forest as forecasters called 
for more thunderstorms today 
about 23000 firefighters were battling blazes on 173000 acres 
in idaho california oregon utah nebraska montana and new 
mexico according to the boise interagency fire center the federal 
wildfire command post 
