<TEXT>
about 150 of the hundreds of east germans 
who have fled their communist homeland through hungary to austria 
left monday for west germany and a new life 
the east germans most in their early 20s and carrying papers 
provided by the west german embassy in vienna boarded one of the 
trains that leave each night with refugees bound for west germany 
embassy spokesmen will not say how many east germans have passed 
through vienna since may when hungarys communist regime began 
dismantling barbed wire fences and fortifications along its border 
with austria 
