peter shaffer took a fresh look at his comedy hit lettice and 
lovage and changed endings and the cast changed last fall 
increasingly london shows are evolving during their runs in 
ways distinct from both the usual recasting and adjustments that 
occur when a show moves to new york or has a long run 
directors and writers are having a second look at their work on 
home turf if need be changes are being made 
the first ending is history shaffer the tonywinning 
author of equus and amadeus said of lettice and lovage 
the comedys october 1987 globe theater debut finished with the 
