<TEXT>
two longtime newspaper rivals the las 
vegas reviewjournal and the las vegas sun announced plans monday 
to merge their business circulation and production operations in a 
joint operating agreement 
the venture must be approved by the us attorney generals 
office if accepted las vegas will become the 20th city in the 
country to have newspapers participating in a joa 
no change of ownership is involved and the agreement calls for 
both newspapers to maintain independent and separate newsrooms as 
well as separate weekday editions under the terms of the joa the 
reviewjournal would remain a morning paper and the sun would 
change from morning to afternoon publication 
combined morning editions labeled the las vegas 
reviewjournalsun would be published on saturdays sundays and 
holidays 
the sun would receive 10 percent of the operating profits of the 
two newspapers and the reviewjournal would receive 90 percent 
based on the rjs stronger financial position according to the 
joa agreement 
the agreement makes financial sense for the reviewjournal and 
is the last hope of the sun to continue providing las vegas with 
an outspoken frequently divergent editorial voice said the text 
of the agreement 
without this move we believe the sun is in probable danger of 
financial failure sun president brian greenspun said in a 
statement monday with this move there will be no displacement 
of sun newsroom personnel and there will be the continuation of an 
important newspaper 
the reviewjournal is the states largest newspaper and is the 
flagship for donrey media group which owns 59 us daily 
newspapers the sun is nevadas thirdlargest newspaper 
as of last year the reviewjournal had a circulation of 121321 
daily and 142923 on sunday the sun had a circulation of 50515 
daily and 54669 on sunday 
the plan would link the business and production functions of the 
two newspapers for an initial period of 50 years 
under the agreement the sun will give donrey media group 10 
percent of the outstanding stock in community cable tv and an 
option to purchase an additional 35 percent of the stock at a later 
date 
the value of 10 percent of community cable tv is estimated at 
about 20 million 
the agreement to enter into the joa was signed june 12 and is to 
be filed with the justice department tuesday approval of such 
agreements can take anywhere from a few months to several years 
the reviewjournalsun filing asked that the agreement be 
approved quickly and without a hearing because of the weak position 
of the sun in the marketplace 
the document said the sun is losing about 3 million a year on 
annual revenues of 21 million the newspaper last made a profit in 
1981 earning 183148 
the suns total debt now exceeds 107 million the application 
said 
the greenspun family has borrowed money from banks and 
familyaffiliated businesses to keep the newspaper going the 
document said hank greenspun founder of the sun died july 22 
 
